{
  "info": {
    "name": "Raajsi - OTP Authentication",
    "_postman_id": "otp-auth-collection-2024",
    "description": "Phone-based OTP authentication using 2Factor.in service\n\n## Features:\n- Send OTP to phone number\n- Verify OTP and get JWT token\n- Resend OTP functionality\n- Rate limiting protection\n\n## Setup:\n1. Set {{baseUrl}} variable (default: http://localhost:5000)\n2. Add TWOFACTOR_API_KEY to backend .env\n3. Start backend server\n4. Import this collection\n5. Test the endpoints!\n\n## Flow:\n1. Send OTP → Get sessionId\n2. User receives SMS\n3. Verify OTP → Get token\n4. Store token in localStorage\n5. Use token for authenticated requests",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Send OTP",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"phoneNumber\": \"+919999999999\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["auth", "send-otp"]
        },
        "description": "Send OTP to user's phone number. Phone number can be in formats:\n- +919999999999\n- 919999999999\n- 9999999999 (assumes India +91)\n\nResponse includes sessionId and OTP (in development mode only)"
      },
